      <body>
         <div type="translation">
            <ab>(Recto);;(Christian symbols). List of clothes which are in the rest-house (praetorium) &lt;or: press-house (pressorium)?&gt;, through brother Martyrios, from me, Zenon: A linen variegated tunic, 1, one; cloaks made in the Antiochian style, 5, in total, five; similarly, an Antioch hood, 1, in total, one; combed linen variegated tunic, 1, in total, one; wrapping clothes, 3, three; a shirt and a cloak; a light-green upper garment, 1, one; embroidered panels, 4, in total, four; a fine linen cloth, 1 in total, one; silver spoons, 10, in total, ten. Give these effects to brother Theodosios, taking from him on account of what he owes to me for  - - -;;(Verso);;A receipt of Zenon - - -.</ab>
         </div>
